fields.text_html:
Welcome  

This is an experiment in the economics of decision-making. The instructions are simple; if you follow them carefully and make good decisions, you can earn a considerable amount of money that will be paid to you privately at the end of the experiment.

In this experiment, your color is #id_label#.

You and the other #player_count-1# people in your group each set a range. The ranges you and your group members select determine your earnings each period.

Continue to the next page of the instructions by pressing the Next   button.

Revenue Bars

Along the horizontal axis there is a set of revenue bars. The higher the bar, the more valuable the bar is. You and the other members in your group will each submit a range using the "Start" and "End" handles at the bottom of your screens. You can select any contiguous range, from one bar up to the entire range of bars. However, anywhere your range overlaps with another person in your group, you must split the revenue of that bar equally. 

You must also pay a cost for each bar in your range, which we represent on the graph with a light #id_label# color. You will lose money if the cost you pay exceeds the revenue you earn for any given bar. Any bar you lose money on will display a "!". The graph displays bars outside of all ranges in a white color. Bars within one or more ranges display a stacked graph of the current occupants.

Try moving the range handles by left-clicking and dragging them to a new position. Do this now.

On the next page, we will display the results.

Continue to the next page of the instructions by pressing the Next   button.

Practice

Press the Send Range   button at the bottom of your screen. Do this now. Your total profit per period is shown as the dark #id_label# area in the graph and reported in the right side of the Group Summary box. Your total cost per period is the light #id_label# area in graph and reported in the left side of the Group Summary box.

Try moving your range around and observing how the Group Summary box changes. Everyone in your group has the same cost for occupying a bar.

You and your group members can update your range anytime during the experiment. Each period lasts #period_length# second(s).

Continue to the next page of the instructions by pressing the Next   button.

Conclusion

You can use the help buttons  to reference the instructions during the experiment.

Once everyone completes the instructions, the ranges will reset. Everyone must press a Ready to Start button at the bottom of the screen before anyone can submit a range.

This is the end of the instructions. If you have any questions, please raise your hand, and a monitor will come by to answer them. If you are finished with the instructions, please click the Start   button located in the bottom right of this frame. The instructions will remain on your screen until the experiment begins. We need everyone to click the Start   button before we can begin the experiment.

fields.title: Chat
fields.text:
Chat

You are free to discuss any aspects of the experiment, with the following exceptions: you may not reveal your name, discuss side payments outside the laboratory, or engage in inappropriate language (including such shorthand as ‘WTF’). If you do, you will be excused and forgo your experiment earnings.

Chatting is disabled once the next set of periods begins.

fields.title: Graph - Preserve Order
fields.text:
Graph

Along the horizontal axis there is a set of revenue bars. The higher the bar, the more valuable the bar is. You and the other members in your group will each submit a range using the "Start" and "End" handles at the bottom of your screens. You can select any contiguous range, from one bar up to the entire range of bars. However, anywhere your range overlaps with another person in your group, you must split the revenue of that bar equally. 

You must also pay a cost for each bar in your range, which we represent on the graph with a light #id_label# color. You will lose money if the cost you pay exceeds the revenue you earn for any given bar. Any bar you lose money on will display a "!". The graph displays bars outside of all ranges in a white color. Bars within one or more ranges display a stacked graph of the current occupants.

Two rules are in effect for allowable ranges. The first rule is that your range's midpoint, which we display as a circle in the middle of your range, cannot go past your immediate neighbors' midpoint. The second rule is that you cannot move your range into another group member's range unless they are your immediate neighbor.

fields.title: Period Block 2
fields.text:
Update

Before the next set of periods begins, you can chat with the other people in your group using the form in the bottom right corner of your screen. You are free to discuss any aspects of the experiment, with the following exceptions: you may not reveal your name, discuss side payments outside the laboratory, or engage in inappropriate language (including such shorthand as ‘WTF’). If you do, you will be excused and forgo your experiment earnings.

You and your other group members can transfer profits to each other using the form in the bottom left corner of your screen. The amount of the transfer is in whole US Cents (¢).

Once you have ready, press the Ready to Start button. Once everyone has pressed Ready to Start, you can update your ranges, but chatting and profit transfers are disabled.

fields.title: Period Block 3
fields.text:
Update

Two new rules are now in effect for allowable ranges. The first rule is that your range's midpoint, which we display as a circle in the middle of your range, cannot go past your immediate neighbors' midpoint. The second rule is that you cannot move your range into another group member's range unless they are your immediate neighbor.

These rules apply to all members of your group.

Once you have ready, press the Ready to Start button. Once everyone has pressed Ready to Start, you can update your ranges, but chatting and profit transfers are disabled.

fields.title: Transfer Cents
fields.text:
Transfer Profits

You and your other members of your group can transfer profits to each other using this form. The amount of the transfer is in whole US Cents (¢).

Transfers are disabled once the next set of periods begins.
